Package org.strykeforce.deadeye

Provides a Java client library for the Stryke Force FRC Deadeye Vision System. The most important class is Deadeye, which represents a connected Deadeye camera pipeline and is the starting point for using this library. A client (robot) can receive target data updates by implementing the TargetDataListener interface and registering it with a Deadeye instance.

Classes UprightRectTargetData, MinAreaRectTargetData, and TargetListTargetData are interfaces to the default Deadeye camera pipelines. Custom pipelines can be created by subclassing TargetData and providing a corresponding DeadeyeJsonAdapter.

Classes Point and Point2D are utility classes used by the TargetData classes.

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DeadeyeJsonAdapter<T extends TargetData>
    A TargetData class implements DeadeyeJsonAdapter to enable serialization and deserialization from JSON.
    TargetDataListener<T extends TargetData>
    A class implements TargetDataListener to receive updates of the specifed TargetData from a Deadeye camera pipeline.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Deadeye<T extends TargetData>
    Objects of the Deadeye class represent a connection to a Deadeye camera pipeline.
    Deadeye.Capture
    An Capture represents Deadeye capture configuration information.
    Deadeye.Info
    An Info represents Deadeye pipeline configuration information.
    MinAreaRectTargetData
    A MinAreaRectTargetData represents data returned from a Deadeye MinAreaRectPipeline.
    Point
    A point representing a location in (x,y) coordinate space, specified in integer precision.
    Point2D
    A point representing a location in (x,y) coordinate space, specified in double precision.
    TargetData
    TargetData is an base class for target data sent by Deadeye camera pipelines.
    TargetListTargetData
    A TargetListTargetData represents data returned from a Deadeye TargetListPipeline.
    TargetListTargetData.Target
    A Target represents a single target returned in a TargetListTargetData.
    UprightRectTargetData
    A UprightRectTargetData represents data returned from a Deadeye UprightRectPipeline.
